            <div type="translation" resp="#JP">
                <p>To Titus Fulvius (Fulvus) Aurelius Antoninus, son of Imperator Caesar Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Augustus. Lucius Aponius Rufinus (set this up) to mark the honour of his holding of the sevirate, at his own expense.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><ref target="https://pir.bbaw.de/id/2541">Titus Aurelius Fulvus Antoninus </ref> was the short-lived twin brother of the emperor Commodus, son of the emperor M. Aurelius, born at Lanuvium on 31 August 161, and died in 165. His name often appears in the form Fulvius, as here.<!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--to Titus Fulvius Aurelius Antoninus, son of Marcus Aurelius; NB, reused for a C4/5 AD honorfic on reverse (AE 1906.75.ii).Text: T. Fulvio Aurelio Antonino Imp. Caes. M. Aureli. Antonini. Aug. filio. L. Aponius Rufinus ob honorem seviratus pec.sua.--></p>
            </div>
